snippet.textDisplay:
ASMR rules for ASMRtist by ASMR viewers
(taken from comments)
if this comment was posted on your video, you have at least one of these(it will be highlighted):
1. try to stay away from making patterns or rythms
2. don't speak fast, unless it's inaudible
3. don't go from whispering to soft spoken (soft spoken to whispering is okay)
4. don't blow to loudly into the mic causing to high desible that makes us not hear anything at all
5. try to use ads at the beginning of a video, mid or after the video is rough on us
6. if you're doing a trigger video, try to keep them even, like 5 min each or more or less
If i find more comments that many ppl agree with then ill add it to the list.
no ASMRtist should take this personally this is just help :D
snippet.textOriginal:
ASMR rules for ASMRtist by ASMR viewers 
(taken from comments)
if this comment was posted on your video, you have at least one of these(it will be highlighted):
1. *try to stay away from making patterns or rythms*
2. don't speak fast, unless it's inaudible
3. don't go from whispering to soft spoken (soft spoken to whispering is okay)
4. don't blow to loudly into the mic causing to high desible that makes us not hear anything at all
5. *try to use ads at the beginning of a video, mid or after the video is rough on us*
6. if you're doing a trigger video, try to keep them even, like 5 min each or more or less
